<dl id="n35228e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35228e">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35228e"> 228(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bells hung in / porch 20 paces / from church</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Orthodox Greek churches are <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> usually surmounted by two or three towers, but the <mark>bells are hung in a kind of wooden porch, resembling a lych-gate, and standing about twenty paces from the church</mark>. <small> &ldquo;BUCHAREST&rdquo; <a name="EBBH" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBBH"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 717-8</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
